ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.86                 Enzyme
NAME        7-epi-alpha-selinene synthase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     (2E,6E)-farnesyl-diphosphate diphosphate-lyase (7-epi-alpha-selinene-forming)
REACTION    (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate = 7-epi-alpha-selinene + diphosphate [RN:R09886]
ALL_REAC    R09886
SUBSTRATE   (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C00448]
PRODUCT     7-epi-alpha-selinene [CPD:C20159];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     The recombinant enzyme from Vitis vinifera forms 49.5% (+)-valencene (cf. EC 4.2.3.73, valencene synthase) and 35.5% (-)-7-epi-alpha-selinene. Initial cyclization gives (+)-germacrene A in an enzyme bound form which is not released to the medium.
